<p>A <b>military parade</b> (<b>square bashing</b> in British military slang) is a formation of soldiers whose movement is restricted by close-order manoeuvring known as <b>drilling</b> or <b>marching</b>. The American usage is "<b>formation</b> or <b>military review</b>". The <a href="Military" title="Military">military</a> <a href="Parade" title="Parade">parade</a> is now almost entirely ceremonial, though soldiers from <a href="Time_immemorial" title="Time immemorial">time immemorial</a> up until the late 19th century fought in formation. Massed parades may also hold a role for propaganda purposes, being used to exhibit the apparent military strength of one's nation.</p>
